MALE (n= 5
). Smaller than female, 162–172, 59 – 66 wide. Gnathosoma 18–20 ; basal seta ( ep ) 3 ; antapical seta ( d ) moderately long and bifurcate 11–13 ; chelicerae 10–11 . Prodorsal shield as in female, 45–50, 55 – 60 wide. Scapular seta ( sc ) 4–5, 22 – 26 apart. Legs as in female.
